<P>
   EDS: Here are the articles on the arrest of Wen Ho Lee that are
being planned by The New York Times for papers of Saturday, Dec.
11.
</P>
<P>
   (Stories will move in NATIONAL ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SPYING-RDP (Washington) _ Fired scientist Wen Ho Lee was
indicted Friday for removing nuclear secrets from a secured
computer at the Los Alamos weapons lab where he worked. FBI agents
immediately arrested Lee at his home outside of Los Alamos, N.M. By
James Risen and David Johnston.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SPYING-SECRETS (Washington) _ What is the evidence
presented in the indictment, and what does it show, beyond what we
already know, about the larger allegations on the one side of
espionage and on the other side that this is selective prosecution?
By James Risen and David Johnston.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SPYING-TRIAL (Washington) _ What are the laws, the issues
and the history of conducting trials when one issue for prosecutors
is how much to reveal of national secrets. By Raymond Bonner.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SPYING-DEFENSE (Albuquerque, N.M.) _ Developing: Story on
anything Wen Ho Lee or his lawyers say following his arrest. By
Sandra Blakeslee.
</P>
